      "text": "VIA E-TARIFF DELIVERY\n\nFebruary 21, 2025\n\nMs. Stephanie Cook \nChief Clerk \nIllinois Commerce Commission \n527 E. Capitol Avenue \nSpringfield, IL 62701 \nRe: Rate Design Investigation (RDI) Compliance Filing ICC Docket No. 24-0378 Revised \nRider NS and Delivery Service Charges Informational Sheets \nDear Ms. Cook: \nCommonwealth Edison Company (ComEd) submits to the Illinois Commerce \nCommission (ICC) the following revised tariff and informational sheets for filing pursuant \nto the ICC’s Order dated January 16, 2025, in Docket No. 24-0378. These informational \nsheets are revised from the sheets submitted on January 30, 2025 and are in \ncompliance with the aforementioned Order. They are to become effective February 28, \n2025, seven days after the filing date, consistent with the same timing of the previous \nfiling. \n\nCOMMONWEALTH EDISON COMPANY ELECTRICITY ILL. C. C. No. 10 Rider NS 2nd Revised Sheet No. 277.1 canceling 1st Revised Sheet No. 277.1\n\nDelivery Service Charges Informational Sheets 5th Revised Informational Sheet No. 64.3 canceling 4th Revised Informational Sheet No. 64.3 5th Revised Informational Sheet No. 64.5 canceling 4th Revised Informational Sheet No. 64.5 5th Revised Informational Sheet No. 64.7 canceling 4th Revised Informational Sheet No. 64.7 5th Revised Informational Sheet No. 64.9 canceling 4th Revised Informational Sheet No. 64.9 4th Revised Informational Sheet No. 64.11 canceling 3rd Revised Informational Sheet No. 64.11 4th Revised Informational Sheet No. 64.13 canceling 3rd Revised Informational Sheet No. 64.13 4th Revised Informational Sheet No. 64.15 canceling 3rd Revised Informational Sheet No. 64.15\n\nMs. Stephanie Cook February 21, 2025 \nCompliance Filing ICC Docket No. 24-0378 \n2 \n\nAfter discussions with ICC Staff and parties interested in the application of Rider NS – \nNonstandard Services and Facilities (“Rider NS”) and the allocation of Beneficial \nElectrification (BE) costs, ComEd is making the following updates: \n1) Revisions to Rider NS to make clarifications in the follow subsections: (a)(1) \nremove the term “to the extent known and”, (b) & (d) add “business” to make it “14 \nbusiness days”, and (d) add “that was signed and approved by the customer per \nsubsection c”. \n2) Revision to the determination of nonresidential Delivery Service Charges in the \nEmbedded Cost of Service Studies (ECOSS) and rate design models. Specifically, \nthe Final Order stated: “The Commission finds ComEd’s BE Plan cost allocation \nas updated throughout this proceeding and supported by Staff reasonable and it \nis adopted.” Docket No. 24-0378 Final Order at 84. ComEd witness Leick made \na revision to ComEd’s proposal for the allocation of BE costs to exclude the High \nVoltage (“HV”) billing demand. Leick Rebuttal, ComEd Ex. 5.0, 19:353-358 & \n21:379-386. Staff did not raise any concerns with this proposed revision. Sanders \nRebuttal, Staff Ex. 5.0, 13:277-18:372. Therefore, the HV billing demand should \nhave been excluded in the allocation of BE cost allocation and this revised filing \nmakes that adjustment. \nThe updated 2026 and 2027 Embedded Cost of Service Studies (ECOSS) and rate \ndesign models are being sent electronically to Mr. Christopher Boggs (Rates Analyst), \nMr. Curtis Sanders (Rates Analyst), Mr. Robert Martin (Rate Analyst), Mr. Daniel \nAshbaugh (Electrical Engineer), Ms. Jennifer Morris (Assistant Director), Mr. Leonard \nHamidu (Rate Analyst), Ms. Tanya Capellan (Director), Mr. Jim Zolnierek (Chief - Public \nUtilities Bureau), Mr. Richard Bridal (Director), Ms. Rochelle Phipps (Senior Financial \nAnalyst) and Mr. Scott Struck (Director). \nElectronic copies of this transmittal letter and informational sheets are being provided to \nMr. Boggs, Mr. Sanders, Mr. Martin, Mr. Ashbaugh, Ms. Morris, Mr. Hamidu, Ms. \nCapellan, Mr. Zolnierek, Mr. Bridal, Ms. Phipps, Mr. Struck, and Mr. Sam McClerren \n(Tariff Analyst). Furthermore, these documents along with the revised ECOSS and rate \ndesign models are also being submitted on e-Docket and thereby being made available \ngenerally. \n\nMs. Stephanie Cook February 21, 2025 \nCompliance Filing ICC Docket No. 24-0378 \n3 \n\nSincerely,\n\nJohn L. Leick \nSenior Manager Retail Rates \nComEd \n(779) 231-2375 \ncc: Mr. Christopher Boggs Ms. Jennifer Morris \nMr. Curtis Sanders Mr. Leonard Hamidu \nMr. Robert Martin Ms. Tanya Capellan \nMr. Daniel Ashbaugh Mr. Jim Zolnierek \nMr. Richard Bridal Ms. Rochelle Phipps \nMr. Scott Struck Mr. Sam McClerren \nILL. C. C. No. 10 \nCommonwealth ELECTRICITY 2nd Revised Sheet No. 277.1 \nEdison Company (Canceling 1st Revised Sheet No. 277.1) \nRIDER NS \nNONSTANDARD SERVICES AND FACILITIES \n(Continued from Sheet No. 277) \n\n(Continued on Sheet No. 278) Filed with the Illinois Commerce Commission on Date Effective: February 28, 2025 February 21, 2025. Issued pursuant to the Issued by David R. Perez, EVP and COO Illinois Commerce Commission Order dated Post Office Box 805379 January 16, 2025 in Docket No. 24-0378. Chicago, Illinois 60680-5379 Asterisk (*) indicates change.\n\n* The Company furnishes, installs, owns, operates, replaces, and maintains nonstandard services and facilities, subject to the following conditions: a. Beginning January 1, 2026, if the estimated cost of the nonstandard services and facilities installation exceeds the cost of a standard services and facilities installation by more than $100,000, prior to entering into the written agreement specified in subpart (c) below, the Company will provide the retail customer with a Preliminary Assessment of the nonstandard services and facilities. The Preliminary Assessment shall: 1. detail with specificity all proposed new services and facilities and explain why the nonstandard services and facilities qualify as larger, more, or different services and/or facilities; 2. explain whether a portion of such nonstandard services and facilities may reasonably be used for 